    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
          <p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>371 Walnut St</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">near <placeName>13th St</placeName></p>
			<p>For</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">The <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)"><placeName><hi rend="underline">America</hi></placeName></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>London</placeName> <date>29th Tebet 5611</date></p>
			<p>Revd and dear Sir&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">I have <sic>considerd</sic> it a religious duty<lb/> on my part to address this day a Pastoral letter to the<lb/> much respect <persName>A. Hart Esq.</persName> President of your Congregation<lb/> to endeavour a reconciliation for indeed I must confess<lb/> fearless of any one that you Sir as a <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> cannot in any way be removed unless proper evidence<lb/> of any <add>Hebrew</add> be regularly taken by Orthodox and<lb/> authenticated Jewish Ecclesiastics&#44; thus I says if they<lb/> really wish to be reputed as Jews which I doubt<lb/> not but they are I have written to say that I am in<lb/> full hopes that shortly every member at <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> will loudly cry <add>Hebrew</add> I regret that<lb/> the days are very short &#40;<date>Friday&#39;s</date>&#41; and my occupations<lb/> are numerous otherwise I should send you a copy<lb/> I trust they will do all that is right. I have read<lb/> the whole of your letter attentively&#8212;now my Dr.<lb/> friend let me urge upon you and request it as a<lb/> particular favor as a brother or a child pray give<lb/> in &#40;consistently&#41; in whatever you can <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> pray <sic>dont</sic> be hasty till all over <add>Hebrew</add> <sic>dont</sic> allow your<lb/> enemies to laugh&#44; enter&#44; be reinstated&#8212;<add>Hebrew</add> I doubt<lb/> not you will do it and will fully understand my meaning and<lb/> feelings&#8212;write to me <sic>dont</sic> spare me point out to me I am ready<lb/> and willing to serve you as I see you are in the right</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p>I hope <persName>Mr. Hart</persName> will be generous to show you<lb/> my letter and communicate it at once to the<lb/> authorities and do all in your favor<add>&#63;</add><lb/> as for your advice to the gang man here<lb/> to hesitate &#38;c I said nothing to him for<lb/> heaven knows he might take it as if I had<lb/> some particular views in it therefore silence on my part was the best&#8212;he is rather sly &#38;<lb/> I cannot find out what nature of a letter<lb/> he wrote &#40;though he is <hi rend="underline">very friendly with me</hi>&#41;<lb/> to your congregation&#44; what are his pretensions&#63; in a<lb/> place they had you your Sermons&#44; your literature<lb/> <del>a toll</del> an entire <sic><hi rend="underline">beginer</hi></sic> in every thing <del>he is past</del><lb/> it is only 4 years he is here <del>&#63;</del><lb/> I thought therefore prudently not<lb/> to say a word to him&#44; <del>though</del> I <sic>learnt</sic> that he<lb/> wishes to be insured of the situation before he goes&#44;<lb/> indeed&#8212;on what ground&#63; I shall be most happy to<lb/> hear from you and hope the result will be good&#8212;<lb/> and favourable on your side&#59; let me know something<lb/> of the above going man&#39;s application from here<lb/> let all this be in confidence. wishing you every<lb/> success and prosperity&#8212;I remain</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)">Revd Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)">yours very truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">David Meldola</persName></p>
			<p>The <persName>Revd. Dr. Schiller</persName> has been<lb/> <sic>choosen</sic> as minister &#40;not <add>Hebrew</add>&#41; of <placeName>Manchester</placeName><lb/> this is a <sic>begining</sic> a Cardinal only&#44; at present&#44; <hi rend="underline">he</hi><lb/> indeed is the ally the <hi rend="underline">man</hi>&#8212;<add>Hebrew</add><lb/> not the mere puff and humbugary of initials <persName>Dr Ph<add>&#63;</add></persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Please let me know candidly the effect of my letter<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add></p>
		<pb n="4"/>
			<p>Let me request of you that any thing I might<lb/> have said to be in the <hi rend="underline">greatest confidence</hi><lb/> as the young man is quite on friendly terms<lb/> with me and should not wish him to think<lb/> that I have even mentioned his name<lb/> <persName>Rabbi Nissim</persName> is at present at <placeName>Paris</placeName><lb/> on his journey&#8212;<persName>Mr D Pizinbert</persName> respects<lb/> <hi rend="underline">pray secrecy&#58;</hi></p>
         
        </body>
